channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WATCH: Israel Hacked Pagers of Hezbollah Fighters and Made Them Explode, Hundreds of Injuries Reported
New Trump website reveals how much money a Harris presidency could cost taxpayers
item.description: The Trump campaign released a website Tuesday tabulating how much in increased taxes residents in each state can expect to pay if the 2017 tax cuts expire next year.

item.title: Harris Cites Trump's Abortion Policy for Pregnancy-Related Death
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris is blaming the "consequences of Donald Trump's actions" for a restrictive abortion law in Georgia after a report found that a woman died from infection after a hospital's delay in performing a critical procedure.

item.title: Gov Sanders hits campaign trail as top surrogate for Trump in key battleground state: 'Going full-speed ahead'
item.description: Arkansas Gov. Sarah Huckabee Sanders is ramping up her presence on the campaign trail to support former President Donald Trump and will be taking a more prominent role as a surrogate ahead of the election.

item.title: DOJ: Russian National Arrested for Illegal Export of Drone Technology
item.description: A Russian national residing in Sarasota, Florida, was arrested Monday on charges of smuggling, money laundering, and illegally exporting to Russia technology that could be used in drone production, the U.S. Department of Justice said.

item.title: Hillary Clinton Goes Wild With Disturbing Comments on Trump and Free Speech, JD Vance Responds
UN ambassador criticizes Israeli military, calls for 'fundamental changes'
item.description: United States' Ambassador to the United Nations Linda Thomas-Greenfield told the UN Security Council on Monday that Israel has "no basis" for firing on UNRWA personnel

item.title: WSJ: Authorities Warned About Suspected Trump Gunman
item.description: The suspect arrested after the second assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump reportedly had been flagged previously for erratic behavior concerning Ukraine.

item.title: Pure Gold: JD Vance Blasts Dem/Media Hypocrisy Over Rhetoric
Haitian influx causing one major safety concern among Springfield residents
item.description: Longtime residents of Springfield, Ohio, expressed concerns for their safety, but some also argued the city has an opportunity to give migrants a better life in the U.S.

item.title: Josh Hawley Releases Whistleblower Report on 1st Trump Assassination Attempt
item.description: Teams of Secret Service agents paired with state and local law enforcement to handle reports of suspicious persons were absent from the location of the first assassination attempt on Donald Trump, according to a whistleblower report released by Sen. Josh Hawley.

item.title: Trump Golf Partner Describes 2nd Assassination Attempt: 'I Actually Feel Blessed That I Was There'
Obama makes TikTok appearances to push for voter registration: report
item.description: Barack Obama partnered with a TikTok influencer for National Voter Registration Day in a bid to pull the lever among young Americans for Kamala Harris.

item.title: Trump Returns to Campaign Trail After Weekend Assassination Scare
item.description: Donald Trump hits the campaign trail again Tuesday, traveling to Michigan two days after an apparent assassination attempt against him was foiled at his golf course in Florida.
